
Configure solr
-Download and unzip Solr from http://archive.apache.org/dist/lucene/solr/"version"
-Start the solr. ./bin/solr start
-Start a new core. ./bin/solr create -c "nlp_core2"
-Change the managed-schema to add feature table schema
-run indexer.py to index the features of the corpus to solr.
-Run project_main.py
- Input test sentence and the program will output the table of the features of the question. Top 10 results of weighted and non-weighted search from solr are displayed.
